    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. Figure 1 is located directly above Figure 2. An x axis with the values negative A, 0, and positive A, from left to right, is drawn between the two figures. In Figure 1, a block on a horizontal surface is attached to one end of a stretched horizontal spring. The other end of the spring is attached to a wall.&nbsp;The left side of the block is at position positive A on the x axis. In Figure 2, the spring is no longer being stretched, and the left side of the block is at position negative A on the x axis.\" src=\"/images/0592f7f1992eafe84a541c9b8475f438.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block is attached to one end of a horizontal ideal spring whose other end is attached to a wall. The spring is initially unstretched and its right end is at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 0\"><math alttext=\"x equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>. The block is then pulled until it is at a position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals positive A\"><math alttext=\"x equals positive A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, where the spring exerts a force of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> on the block. The spring is then moved to a position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals negative A\"><math alttext=\"x equals negative A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"